<ContentDialog x:ConnectionId='1'
    x:Class="Folder_Prettifier.Dialogs.UserBenefits"
    xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation"
    xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml"
    xmlns:local="using:Folder_Prettifier.Dialogs"
    xmlns:d="http://schemas.microsoft.com/expression/blend/2008"
    xmlns:mc="http://schemas.openxmlformats.org/markup-compatibility/2006"
    mc:Ignorable="d"
    Title="Benefits of being a authenticated user"
    CloseButtonText="Got it"
                                  >

    <StackPanel>
        <TextBlock Margin="0,0,0,10">User having authenticated will enjoy the following features of the application</TextBlock>

        <TextBlock FontSize="20" FontWeight="Medium" Margin="0,15,0,5">Cloud services are available to sync</TextBlock>
        <TextBlock TextWrapping="WrapWholeWords">
            Access to the cloud services like Google Drive, Microsoft OneDrive, Dropbox &amp; Mega
            will be unlocked. Having that access you can consume the functionality of folder sync
            with cloud to sync your files between your service provider	&amp; your windows 10 device.
        </TextBlock>

        <TextBlock FontSize="20" FontWeight="Medium" Margin="0,15,0,5">Backup settings on cloud</TextBlock>
        <TextBlock TextWrapping="WrapWholeWords">
            With your Folder Prettifier account, you can sync your settings with the cloud so that they remain safe &amp;
            secure throught the time you use this product. They will be stored on the cloud	&amp; you can
            restore them anytime you want from the settings. This sync will save your time of personalization
            if you, in future, move to a new machine. This all with a seamless experience.
        </TextBlock>

        <TextBlock FontSize="20" FontWeight="Medium" Margin="0,15,0,5">Personalized catalog</TextBlock>
        <TextBlock TextWrapping="WrapWholeWords">
            Having your Folder Prettifier account with you, you will be able to personalize your
            personal folder catalog. A catalog is just a blueprint of your folders. This catalog will
            be kept on cloud. So, it's persistent.
        </TextBlock>

        <TextBlock FontSize="20" FontWeight="Medium" Margin="0,15,0,5">Customs icons are saved on cloud</TextBlock>
        <TextBlock TextWrapping="WrapWholeWords">
            If you have added custom icons to your folders for the better identification purpose then this will
            help you keep your folder icons persistent in the future &amp; you don't need to create a dedicated
            folder just for icons.
        </TextBlock>
    </StackPanel>
</ContentDialog>
 

